    "name": "Light Whales",
    "profile": "\"A Native american came from a future videogame to steal your soul\".\r\n\r\nBorn in 2016, Light Whales are the brainchild of Jack Pallaver. The project came to life with the completion of their debut album \"Feel Alone with the Science,\" an entirely self-produced work created using only \"modest\" means. Recorded at home with a cellphone, a computer, and an SM57 microphone, the album echoes the sounds of MGMT, Beck, and the alternative indie vibes of the 2000s.\r\n\r\nTo bring the album to the stage, Jack sought the help of local musicians he admired: Sebastiano Cecchini from Humus on drums, Matteo Tomaselli from Bob and the Apple on keyboards, and Andrea Garofalo on bass and guitar. After a few years of intense live activity, the band took a break to focus on producing a second album, once again crafted solo and home-made.\r\n\r\nIn 2024, Light Whales return with \"Death to the Whales.\" This new chapter for the band is a sonic journey that expands and enriches their musical experience.\r\n\r\nGiacomo Pal",
